## Lifecycle Handling in ViewModel

### Use `OnLifecycleEventEffect` Instead of Raw `DisposableEffect`

Use the `OnLifecycleEventEffect` helper from `coreui.extensions` instead of the boilerplate `DisposableEffect + LifecycleEventObserver` pattern. It wraps the callback in `rememberUpdatedState` to prevent stale lambdas.

```kotlin
import com.shodo.android.coreui.extensions.OnLifecycleEventEffect

// ON_START: reload when screen is first shown (after Activity.start())
OnLifecycleEventEffect(Lifecycle.Event.ON_START, lifecycleOwner) { viewModel.start() }

// ON_RESUME: reload every time screen comes back to foreground (e.g., after camera)
OnLifecycleEventEffect(Lifecycle.Event.ON_RESUME, lifecycleOwner) { viewModel.start() }
```

Use `ON_RESUME` when data can change while the user is in another Activity (e.g., a camera flow). Use `ON_START` for all other cases.

