## Data Mapping

### ✅ Put Mappers in the `uimodel` Package — Not in the ViewModel

Extension functions that convert domain entities → UI models belong in the `uimodel/` package alongside the UI data classes (e.g., `MyFeatureUI.kt`). This follows the same pattern as `MyFriendUI.kt`.

```kotlin
// ✅ GOOD: Mapper in uimodel/MyFeatureUI.kt
fun User.mapToMyFeatureUI() = MyFeatureUI(
    id = id,
    name = name
)

// ✅ GOOD: ViewModel just calls it
val uiItems = withContext(Dispatchers.Default) {
    users.map { it.mapToMyFeatureUI() }.toPersistentList()
}
```

```kotlin
// ❌ BAD: private mapper defined at the bottom of the ViewModel file
private fun User.mapToUI() = MyFeatureUI(...)
```

Rationale: keeps ViewModels focused on state management, mappers are independently testable, and the location is consistent across all features.

### ❌ Don't expose domain models in UI State
```kotlin
// BAD
data class Data(val users: List<User>) : UiState()

// GOOD
data class Data(val users: PersistentList<UserUI>) : UiState()
```

